This document includes:

* General information
* Licensing
* Requirements


* General information

GemVt is the GNU Emulator of a Virtual Terminal for the X Window System
written on top of the Gtk+ toolkit.

This is beta software.


* Licensing

The Gtk+ widgets GtkTerm, GtkTty (together with GtkEmuVt) and GtkLed are
released under the terms of the GNU LGPL (GNU LIBRARY GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE).
Read the file COPYING.LIB for more information.

The rest of the code is released under the terms of the GNU GPL (GNU GENERAL
PUBLIC LICENSE).
Read the file COPYING for more information.

* Requirements

The GemVt program along with it's widgets depends on a couple of extra packages
for working properly:

	- The latest Gtk+: This is the release of the Gtk+ toolkit.
	  You can find Gtk+ releases at:
	  
	  ftp://ftp.gimp.org/pub/gtk/


* Getting GemVt

GemVt has it's own web page from which you can get the latest release:

http://www.SoftHome.net/pub/users/timj/gemvt/index.htm


Have fun,

	Tim Janik <timj@gimp.org>
